82.5	A_Clockwork_Orange_(film)	A Clockwork Orange (film)	A Clockwork Orange is a 1971 film adaptation of Anthony Burgess's 1962 novel of the same name. It was written, directed and produced by Stanley Kubrick. It features disturbing, violent images, facilitating its social commentary on psychiatry, youth gangs, and other social, political, and economic subjects in a dystopian, future Britain.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Clockwork_orangeA.jpg/220px-Clockwork_orangeA.jpg
